 To solve the equation $\left(\frac{3}{4}\right)^x=\frac{81}{256}$, we need to take the logarithm of both sides to isolate $x$. We have:\begin{align*}
\log\left(\left(\frac{3}{4}\right)^x\right) &= \log\left(\frac{81}{256}\right).
\end{align*}Taking the logarithm of $\frac{81}{256}$ can be done using the change of base formula: $$x\log\left(\frac{4}{3}\right) = \log\left(\frac{81}{256}\right).$$Simplifying the left side gives $x\log\left(\frac{3}{4}\right) = \log\left(\frac{81}{256}\right)$. Dividing both sides by $\log\left(\frac{3}{4}\right)$ gives: $$x = \frac{\log\left(\frac{81}{256}\right)}{\log\left(\frac{3}{4}\right)}.$$Using a calculator to compute the values, we get $x \approx \boxed{6}$.
